+# Analytics Dashboard API Implementation Plan
+
+> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.
+
+**Goal:** Build a multi-tenant analytics dashboard API with user management, event ingestion, query engine, dashboard CRUD, and data export.
+
+**Architecture:** Express REST API with SQLite (better-sqlite3) persistence, JWT auth, tenant isolation via middleware. Modular route files per domain (auth, events, queries, dashboards, export). Shared DB module and auth middleware.
+
+**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ES2022, Node16), Express, better-sqlite3, jsonwebtoken, uuid, bcrypt-less (use crypto for hashing)
+
+---
+
+### Task 1: Database Module
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/db.ts`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+```typescript
+// src/db.ts
+import Database from 'better-sqlite3';
+import path from 'node:path';
+import fs from 'node:fs';
+
+let db: Database.Database | null = null;
+
+export function getDb(dbPath?: string): Database.Database {
+  if (db) return db;
+  db = new Database(dbPath || ':memory:');
+  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');
+  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');
+  initSchema(db);
+  return db;
+}
+
+export function initSchema(database: Database.Database): void {
+  const schemaPath = path.resolve(__dirname, '..', 'schema.sql');
+  const schema = fs.readFileSync(schemaPath, 'utf-8');
+  database.exec(schema);
+}
+
+export function resetDb(): void {
+  db = null;
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+### Task 2: Auth Middleware + Password Hashing
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/auth.ts`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+Use `crypto.pbkdf2Sync` for password hashing (no extra deps). JWT middleware extracts tenant_id and user_id from token.
+
+```typescript
+// src/auth.ts
+import { Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';
+import jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';
+import crypto from 'node:crypto';
+
+export const JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET || 'analytics-dashboard-secret';
+
+export interface AuthPayload {
+  userId: string;
+  tenantId: string;
+  role: string;
+}
+
+export interface AuthRequest extends Request {
+  user?: AuthPayload;
+}
+
+export function hashPassword(password: string): string {
+  const salt = crypto.randomBytes(16).toString('hex');
+  const hash = crypto.pbkdf2Sync(password, salt, 1000, 64, 'sha512').toString('hex');
+  return `${salt}:${hash}`;
+}
+
+export function verifyPassword(password: string, stored: string): boolean {
+  const [salt, hash] = stored.split(':');
+  const computed = crypto.pbkdf2Sync(password, salt, 1000, 64, 'sha512').toString('hex');
+  return hash === computed;
+}
+
+export function generateToken(payload: AuthPayload): string {
+  return jwt.sign(payload, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '24h' });
+}
+
+export function authMiddleware(req: AuthRequest, res: Response, next: NextFunction): void {
+  const header = req.headers.authorization;
+  if (!header || !header.startsWith('Bearer ')) {
+    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Authentication required' });
+    return;
+  }
+  try {
+    const token = header.slice(7);
+    const payload = jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET) as AuthPayload;
+    req.user = payload;
+    next();
+  } catch {
+    res.status(401).json({ error: 'Invalid token' });
+  }
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+### Task 3: Auth Routes (register, login, profile, role change)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/routes/auth.ts`
+
+**Endpoints:**
+- POST /api/auth/register - { email, password, tenantId, role? }
+- POST /api/auth/login - { email, password }
+- GET /api/auth/profile - authenticated user profile
+- PUT /api/auth/users/:userId/role - admin only, change role within tenant
+
+---
+
+### Task 4: Events Routes (ingest single + batch)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/routes/events.ts`
+
+**Endpoints:**
+- POST /api/events - single event { name, properties?, timestamp? }
+- POST /api/events/batch - batch events [{ name, properties?, timestamp? }, ...]
+
+---
+
+### Task 5: Query Routes (count, timeseries, breakdown)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/routes/queries.ts`
+
+**Endpoints:**
+- POST /api/queries/count - { event_name?, start?, end?, filters? }
+- POST /api/queries/timeseries - { event_name?, start?, end?, interval?, filters? }
+- POST /api/queries/breakdown - { event_name?, property, start?, end?, filters? }
+
+---
+
+### Task 6: Dashboard Routes (CRUD)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/routes/dashboards.ts`
+
+**Endpoints:**
+- POST /api/dashboards - { name, config? }
+- GET /api/dashboards - list tenant dashboards
+- GET /api/dashboards/:id - single dashboard
+- PUT /api/dashboards/:id - update
+- DELETE /api/dashboards/:id - delete
+
+---
+
+### Task 7: Export Routes (events CSV/JSON, dashboard export)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/routes/export.ts`
+
+**Endpoints:**
+- GET /api/export/events?format=csv|json
+- GET /api/export/dashboards/:id?format=csv|json
+
+---
+
+### Task 8: App Entry Point (createApp)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/app.ts`
+
+Wire all routes, export `createApp` function.
+
+---
+
+### Task 9: Build, Lint, Test
+
+Run `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, fix any issues.
